article.description: Tajuan Agee notched his first double-double of the season and Iona held off Stetson 60-55 on Friday night for its first win of the season.
article.headline: Agee’s double-double leads Iona past Stetson 60-55
article.linkText: Agee’s double-double leads Iona past Stetson 60-55
article.story: KISSIMMEE, Fla. -- Tajuan Agee notched his first double-double of the season and Iona held off Stetson 60-55 on Friday night for its first win of the season. Agee posted game highs of 15 points and 12 rebounds for the Gaels (1-2). Asante Gist finished with 13 points, six assists and five rebounds, while E.J. Crawford added 10 points, six rebounds and two steals. Jahlil Rawley and reserve Christiaan Jones both scored 11 to pace the Hatters (2-3). Rob Perry and Kenny Aninye scored 10 points apiece. Iona made just 14 of 27 free throws (52%), but Stetson only attempted 12 foul shots, making eight. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- Elements of this story were generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
